task.summary: Reformatted and cleaned up code in the GUI package.
I honestly don't remember what I did.

Huge Update!
Added new GPopUp class that allows stuff to be popped onto the screen. If you click outside the popup they will close. This new mechanic allows simple pages, like edit account, about us, and name a project, to be replaced with popups. Basically any page that does not need to be scrolled on can be replaced with a popup. I think they look super awesome and other than a little bug with text boxes in the background disappearing (not a bug, I had to do that otherwise you couldn't click on the popup) they work really well.
Because of this update I reworked many of the pages.
Projects now no longer can share names.
You can now have a maximum of 10 active projects, this is so that I don't have to make the sidebars scroll.
Names and project names now can be at most 15 characters.
Many 'dangerous' actions (deleting accounts/projects/import) now have a warning message.
About popup now has an image.
Many old pages still exist but are now marked depricated.
This basically has all of the updates that I want. Tomorrow I will try to implement JavaFX graphs because I think they look really good.
More popup updates. Added easter egg.
